en with that box, I always dreamed of an AppleIIc, and couldn't wait for my 6th period computer sciences class to mess around with one. I used to piss my teacher off with..<br /><br />10 Print "DC harDCore Another State of Mind"<br />20 goto 10<br /><br />LOL, the rebel skinhead programmer, go figure. I honestly think I quit programming because of my difficutly with hexidecimal numbers. My sister's husband Dennis, J's uncle, sat me down a couple of years ago and had me thinking outside of the Base10 box within 15 minutes, leaving me wondering why math, algebra in particular left me so dumbfounded back then. I seem to do great now. Geometry pissed me off for a long time. It is like I had this logical mind that was constantly arguing with the common sense section of the brain. I saw no sense in writing a 3 page theorem to explain the triangle had 3 whos angles always added up to the same amount of degrees. I get now that it teaches you to again, think outside the box.<br /><br />On the Raid thing and viruses, I get pissed enough the few times an infection has jumped drives. I am going to look over that site when I get home.<br />
